  "description": "<p>Spectacular renovation, fabulous floorplan, and possibly the best location in Washingtonian Woods backing to parkland, pond, and walking paths! Hardwoods flow from the entry foyer and throughout the main level. The large living room showcases crown molding, recessed lighting, a wood-burning masonry fireplace, and double French doors that open to the expansive tiered deck, while the spacious dining room features beautiful natural views through a large picture window and includes custom built-ins and decorator lighting. The remodeled kitchen is a standout, renovated to include granite countertops, and expansive granite-topped island, custom cabinetry, stainless steel appliances, recessed lighting, a double-door pantry, and a custom coffee station. The adjacent family room is brightened by skylights recessed lighting, and large windows, and features a double-sided masonry fireplace plus access to the attached garage and driveway. The private main-level office with double-door entry and built-ins provides an ideal workspace. The beautifully renovated powder room features decorator lighting, subway tile, designer tile flooring, and custom shelving. Hardwood flooring continues through the upper level hallway. The spacious primary suite includes a versatile sitting room/dressing area and a luxury bedroom retreat with a vaulted ceiling, a generous walk-in closet, and three sets of double-door closets. The fully renovated primary bath features marble and quartz finishes, custom cabinetry, a glass-enclosed shower a compartmented water closet, linen closet, and decorator tile, fixtures, and lighting. Three additional bedrooms are spacious and bright while the beautifully renovated second full bath boasts a solid surface vanity, custom cabinetry, wide plank LVP flooring, and a tub/shower with custom tile surround. The upper level also includes a well-appointed laundry room with a laundry sink, folding counter, hanging rod, and extra cabinetry. The finished lower level offers outstanding additional living space including a large recreation room with recessed lighting and a wood-burning fireplace, a custom-built bar, a versatile game room area, a big bonus room, and a beautifully updated full bath. This level also includes plenty of space for storage and direct access to the patio and backyard. Outside of this phenomenal home offers more lovely spaces in which to relax, entertain, and enjoy the natural views, including the tiered Trex deck, the patio, and the front porch. Additional highlights include a five-year-old roof, solar panels, an electric fence, and major system updates. Set on a picturesque cul-de-sac close to all this sought-after neighborhood has to offer, this home has it all!</p>",
